name: **Inishfesh**
description: Inishfesh L927-921 Sheet 31 Christened by its inhabitants “Inishfox”, there is a sandy beach below an old house painted to Rastifarian nightmare standards. Old ruins nearby. This island reeks of money spent in good times and then abandioned. The decking out front of the hose is impressive, but the Velux in the roof is broken. A double door is boarded up. The interior of the island would be an access challenge.
